        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 3:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Florence, or 25 miles west of Pueblo, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo, Florence, Pueblo West, Pueblo Reservoir, and Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for central and
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
